  <summary date="2021-03-24T19:31:36Z" status="Introduced in House">American Values and Security in International Athletics Act

This bill requires the Department of State to distribute specified briefing materials to individuals representing the United States at international athletic competitions. These materials must contain information on human rights concerns and personal privacy and security risks posed by certain host countries (e.g., specified communist countries and countries that do not meet certain minimum standards with respect to human trafficking and are not making significant efforts to do so).</summary>
